Deltari communities in the delta had the lowest civic standing in the proto-Kowloon settlement structure at the time of condemned-debtor transfers.
The Black Ledger's population lists, reconstructed from Ash Scriptorium cyclic chains, are Deltari-majority in transferred subjects.
Deltari oral tradition preserves accounts of the Black Ledger period that match Scriptorium chain contents without having accessed Scriptorium documents — parallel memory transmission through community practice.
The Neon Covenant's founding design incorporated Deltari hydraulic knowledge partly as institutional acknowledgment of communities whose flood-pattern memory was essential to Kowloon's founding infrastructure.
Deltari communities in modern Kowloon maintain a private archive of the Black Ledger period not part of the Courier Lantern Office's official record — family documents, oath records, and memorial lists transmitted since the founding generation.
The private archive has never been submitted to the official registry; Deltari elders decline to merge it on the grounds that previous institutional contact with their population records produced the Black Ledger.

